{"lemma":"آجِلُو","slug":"آجِلُو","root":"#.ج.ل","root_slug":"_-ج-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ج-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آجِل","root":"أجل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n295","n299","n300","n301","n302","n303","n304","n6042"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a troop of antelopes or buffaloes"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔid͡ʒl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n295","headword_ar":"اَجِلَ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalN","text_ar":"اَجَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, Msb, [as, for instance, a thing purchased, and the price thereof, and a thing promised or threatened or foretold, and also payment for a thing purchased, and the fulfilment of a promise or threat or prediction, and any event,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, delayed, postponed, kept back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and therefore,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"future;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^ax~ara","text_ar":"تَاَخَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajala","text_ar":"اَجَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujuwlN","text_ar":"اُجُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same. (Msb.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jilN","text_ar":"ا=جِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalN","text_ar":"اَجَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The primary signification seems to be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had a term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, appointed for it, at which it should fall due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":25},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come to pass."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalahu","text_ar":"اَجَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajulN","text_ar":"اَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^j~lhu","text_ar":"اجّلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^ojiylN","text_ar":"تَاْجِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jlhu","text_ar":"ا=جلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^aAjalapN","text_ar":"مُوَاجَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TK;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He confined, restricted, restrained, withheld, debarred, hindered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevented, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Hence the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaluwA maAlahumo","text_ar":"اَجَلُوا مَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They confined, restricted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their cattle from the pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajala Ealayohimo $ar~FA","text_ar":"اَجَلَ عَلَيْهِمْ شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ar~a","text_ar":"الشَّرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajolN","text_ar":"اَجْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed against them evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"procured it, to them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (S, in the K “ or ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he excited it, stirred it up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provoked it, against them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or, accord. to AZ,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalotu EalayohimN","text_ar":"اَجَلْتُ عَلَيْهِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I committed a crime against them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and AA says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalabotu Ealayohimo","text_ar":"جَلَبْتُ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jararotu","text_ar":"جَرَرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalotu","text_ar":"اَجَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have one and the same signification. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajala liA^aholihi","text_ar":"اَجَلَ لِاَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) inf. n. as above, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gained, acquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purveyed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercised skill in the management of affairs, for his family."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","Lh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n299","headword_ar":"اَجْلٌ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is originally the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajala $ar~FA","text_ar":"اَجَلَ شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he committed evil; ” and is used to indicate the causation of crimes; and afterwards, by extension of its application, to indicate any causation: (Bd in v. 35:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu mino A^ajolika","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ مِنْ اَجْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A_ijolika","text_ar":"من اـِجْلِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu A^ajolaka","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ اَجْلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijolaka","text_ar":"اـِجْلَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A^ajolaAlika","text_ar":"من اَجْلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A_ijolaAlika","text_ar":"من اـِجْلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jlw","text_ar":"جلو"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which also they are mentioned,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A^ajolAlika","text_ar":"من اَجْلالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A_ijolaAlika","text_ar":"من اـِجْلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the K and in the TA, [belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jl","text_ar":"جل"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino jar~aAka","text_ar":"مِنْ جَرَّاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which means [originally]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of thy committing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ubi suprà:) [and then, by extension of its application, as shown above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because of thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thine act"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on thine account; for thy sake;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^ajolika","text_ar":"لِاَجْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is more common in the present day:] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mno jalalika","text_ar":"منْ جَلَلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^ajolihi kaAna ka*aA","text_ar":"مِنْ اَجْلِهِ كَانَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisababihi","text_ar":"بِسَبَبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Because of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, it was thus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a thing was"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) An instance of its occurrence without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"li","text_ar":"لِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is presented by the saying of 'Adee Ibn-Zeyd,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^ajola A^an~a All~`ha qado faD~alakumo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Because that God hath made you to have excel-lence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath preferred you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n300","headword_ar":"اـِجْلٌ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu mino A_ijolika","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ مِنْ اـِجْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu A_ijolaka","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ اـِجْلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajolN","text_ar":"اَجْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n301","headword_ar":"اَجَلٌ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mughnee, K,) with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, (Mughnee,) is written with kesr and with fet-h [to the medial letter, i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajilo","text_ar":"اَجِلْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalo","text_ar":"اَجَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nEm","text_ar":"نعم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEimN","text_ar":"نَعِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) it is a particle (Mughnee) denoting a reply; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mughnee, K;) importing acknowledgment of the truth of the speaker, to him who gives information; and the making a thing known, to him who asks information; and a promise, to him who seeks, or demands; (Mughnee;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is as thou sayest"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the first case; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same, and in the other cases]; (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basalN","text_ar":"بَسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) therefore it occurs after such sayings as “ Zeyd stood ” and “ did Zeyd stand? ” and “ beat thou Zeyd: ” but ElMálakee restricts the information to that which is affirmative, and the saying expressive of seeking or demanding to that which is without prohibition: and it is said by some that it does not occur after an interrogation: (Mughnee:) Er-Radee says, in the Expos. of the Káfiyeh, after Z and others, that it is to denote acknowledgment of the truth of information, and does not occur after a saying in which is the meaning of seeking, or demanding: (TA:) or, accord. to Z and Ibn-Málik and others, it relates particularly to information: and accord. to Ibn-Kharoof, it occurs mostly after information: (Mughnee:) in the Expos. of the Tes-heel, it is said to be for denoting acknowledgment of the truth of information, past or other, affirmative or negative, and not to occur after an interrogation: (TA:) Akh says that it is better than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mughnee, K *) after information, (Mughnee,) in acknowledging the truth of what is said; (S, Mughnee, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nEm","text_ar":"نعم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is better than it after an interrogation: (S, Mughnee, K:) so that when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawofa ta*ohabu","text_ar":"سَوْفَ تَذْهَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Thou wilt, or shalt, go away], thou sayest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalo","text_ar":"اَجَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Yes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and it is better than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nEm","text_ar":"نعم"},{"kind":"text","text":": but when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ata*ohabu","text_ar":"اَتَذْهَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Wilt thou go away?], thou sayest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nEm","text_ar":"نعم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it is better than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajl","text_ar":"اجل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n302","headword_ar":"اَجَلٌ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (S, K:) its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assigned, appointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"specified, term"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the primary signification: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of falling due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jaAlN","text_ar":"ا=جَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period of"},{"kind":"text","text":"women's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting, before they may marry again, after divorce:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur ii. 231 and 232. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of time, in which falls due a debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEahu A_iy~aAhu A_ilay A^ajalK","text_ar":"بَاعَهُ اـِيَّاهُ اـِلَي اَجَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sold it to him for payment at an appointed period"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~ama Ald~aAraAhima fiY TaEaAmK A_ilay A^ajalK","text_ar":"سَلَّمَ الدَّارَاهِمَ فِى طَعَامٍ اـِلَي اَجَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He delivered the money for wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, to be given at an appointed period"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klA^","text_ar":"كلا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, of death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time in which God has eternally decreed the end of life by slaughter or otherwise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole duration of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its end:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus termed: and his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death, by which it terminates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 17:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed, duration of the life"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaA A^ajaluhu","text_ar":"دَنَا اَجَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His death drew near;"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@sotiyfaA='u AlA^ajali","text_ar":"ا@سْتِيفَا=ءُ الاَجَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the completion of the duration of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) In the Kur vi. 128, (see 2, above,) the meaning is, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"term of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"term of extreme old age:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day of resurrection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, * Jel.) The words of the Kur [vi. 2]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a qaDaY A^ajalFA wa A^ajalN","text_ar":"ثُمَّ قَضَى اَجَلًا وَ اَجَلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masam~aY Einodahu","text_ar":"مَسَمَّى عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then He decreed a term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the term of death, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is a term named with Him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the term of the resurrection:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period between the creation and death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period between death and the resurrection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajl","text_ar":"اجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end of a space of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of sleep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of those who have passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of those who remain and those who are to come:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of remaining in this world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of remaining in the world to come:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or in both instances"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accidental,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajl","text_ar":"اجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of some is by accidental means, as the sword, and drowning, and burning, and eating what disagrees, and other means of destruction; while some have their full periods granted to them and are preserved in health until they die a natural death: or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajl","text_ar":"اجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of some is that of him who dies in a state of happiness and enjoyment; and of others, that of him who reaches a limit beyond which God has no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"?","text_ar":"?"},{"kind":"text","text":"appointed, in the natural course of this world, any one to remain therein; and to both of these, reference is made in the Kur [xvi. 72 and] xxii. 5. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Sometimes, also, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Destruction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus it has been explained as occurring in the Kur [vii. 184], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^ano EasaY A^ano yakuwna qadi A@ qotaraba A^ajaluhumo","text_ar":"وَاَنْ عَسَى اَنْ يَكُونَ قَدِ ا@ قْتَرَبَ اَجَلُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And that, may be, their destruction shall have drawn near"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Msb","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n303","headword_ar":"اَجِلْ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalN","text_ar":"اَجَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n304","headword_ar":"اَجِلٌ","root":"Ajl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jilN","text_ar":"ا=جِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6042","headword_ar":"اَجَلُّ","root":"jl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thicker &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thickest"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaliylN","text_ar":"جَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and] i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoZamu","text_ar":"اَعْظَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, great"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jul~aY","text_ar":"جُلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham. p. 45.) With the article, [as a superlative epithet,] it is applied to God; (S, TA;) and so, by poetic license,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ajolalu","text_ar":"الاَجْلَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}